article.headline: VMI 69, Longwood 64 (OT)
article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. (AP) -- Reggie Williams scored 21 points and Matt Coward had 15 as VMI defeated Longwood 69-64 in overtime Wednesday night. Fred Robinson scored all of his six points on the Keydets' 9-4 run in the overtime period, and Williams contributed the other three. Michael Jefferon led the Lancers (0-9) with 23 points, Maurice Sumter had 18 and Chad Kosmo added 11. VMI and Longwood were tied at 32 and halftime, then ended regulation at 60. Each had 47 rebounds, and the Lancers shot 40.6 percent to 39.1 for the Keydets. The Keydets built leads of as much as nine in both halves.
